TY  - JOUR
AU  - Constantinides, George M.
T1  - A Theory of the Nominal Term Structure of Interest Rates
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/5.4.531
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 5
IS  - 4
SP  - 531
EP  - 552
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - A model of the nominal term structure of interest rates is developed that has a positive and stationary process for the interest rate and delivers closed-form expressions for the prices of discount bonds and European options on bonds. Unlike the one-state-variable version of the Cox, Ingersoll, and Ross (1985) model, this model—even in its one-state-variable version—allows the term premium to change sign as a function of the state and the term to maturity, and also allows for shapes of the yield curve that are observed in the U.S. data but that are disallowed in the Cox, Ingersoll, and Ross model
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/5.4.531
ER  - 



